Students at the University of Zululand are demanding more security after a student was shot at an off-campus residence. Courtesy of #DSTV403 RICHARDS BAY - Students at the University of Zululand are demanding more security after a student was shot at an off-campus residence. READ: University of Zululand students demand improved security Many took to social media to voice their anger. Students say they feel neglected by the university as more killings, shootings, rapes and break-ins continue. READ: UniZulu students demand justice after stabbing incident Thabo Shingange, spokesperson for the South African Union of Students stated this has been an ongoing problem at the university without proactive work to address student centre. Shingange stated more resources should be allocated to student security and develop better accomodation for students.